  "title": "WebSocket shared-auth connections could self-declare elevated scopes",
  "description": "The WebSocket connection message handler's clearUnboundScopes function conditionally skips scope clearing when shared-auth is active or control-UI auth bypass is allowed. A client connecting via shared-auth without a device identity can self-declare elevated operator scopes in its connect parameters and retain them because the guard conditions prevent scope clearing for shared-auth connections.",
